Kardan Surges Most Since May 2009 on Stock Repurchase Plan

-- B y   S u s a n   L e r n e r
-- 
2011-09-26T14:16:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/kardan-heads-for-biggest-gain-in-16-months-on-stock-buyback-plan.html
Kardan NV (KRNV)  soared the most since May
2009 after the investor in water infrastructure, property and
financial services said it will spend as much as 15 million
euros ($20 million) to repurchase shares.  The stock jumped 11 percent to 8.485 shekels at the 4:30
p.m. close in  Tel Aviv , paring the decline this year to 59
percent. The companyâ€™s Amsterdam-traded shares rose 7.5 percent
to 1.692 euros at 3:59 p.m. local time.  The purchases, which would represent a maximum of 8.5
percent of the issued shares, will be made until Nov. 8, the
company said in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
